1. The Data

  • fixed acidity
  • volatile acidity
  • citric acid
  • residual sugar
  • chlorides
  • free sulfur dioxide
  • total sulfur dioxide
  • density
  • pH
  • sulphates
  • alcohol
  • quality (score between 0 and 10)

We can see the following things:

  1. all columns are numeric
  2. no missing values
  3. it is not a big dataset

2.5 Bivariate

GGPair graph

wine_ggpair <- wine_clean
wine_ggpair$quality <- as.factor(wine_ggpair$quality)
ggpairs(wine_ggpair, aes(colour = quality, alpha = 0.4))
